# Memory system review

Joel asked for a holistic review of the entire joelclaw memory system, delivered
as a proper MDSvX Brain page rendered by the wiki (2026-07-17).

## Finish line

- `https://brain.joelclaw.com/joelclaw/resources/memory-system/` returns HTTP
  200 and renders an MDSvX page that is both a **map** (how memory flows:
  capture → condense → store → curate → deliver → grade) and a **health
  review** (a verdict per subsystem: working / wobbly / gap, every claim
  carrying a receipt — a file path, log line, state entry, or commit).
- joelclaw-observer's `.brain` is registered in
  `dark-wizard/brain-roots.json` and its pages render on the wiki.
- The page is written in joel-writing-style (ELI5 but technical, talks TO
  Joel), and states its own maintenance path: when the memory system changes
  materially, the page regenerates from a fresh survey — the wiki's provenance
  commit stamp shows staleness at a glance.

## Vocabulary

- **memory system** — everything that captures, condenses, stores, curates,
  delivers, or grades durable knowledge for Joel and his agents.
- **core loop** — observer capture/rollups/dreams/retros → Brain `.svx` stores
  → neat-memory curation → Telegram delivery → reaction grading.
- **periphery** — memory stores outside the core loop (Claude auto-memory,
  rhizome claims, memory-pulse, Typesense/pdf-brain, voice recall, …): mapped
  and graded lighter, not deep-dived.
- **subsystem** — one reviewable unit of the memory system with its own
  verdict.
- **verdict** — one of `working` (does its job, receipts prove it), `wobbly`
  (exists but degraded, misconfigured, or unproven), `gap` (should exist and
  doesn't, or exists and nothing consumes it).

## Notes

- Execution is authorized: workers survey read-only; the steering session
  edits `brain-roots.json`, writes the page, runs the wiki build on flagg,
  200-checks, and DMs the link.
- Skills every session should consult: `joel-writing-style` (the page's
  voice), `herdr-orchestration` (fan-out mechanics), wiki law
  `joelclaw-wiki/AGENTS.md` (Fabrication Rule, privacy exclusions).
- Joel's calls (2026-07-17): page = map + health verdicts; scope = core loop
  deep + periphery mapped; home = `joelclaw` root, and register the observer
  brain as a wiki root in the same effort.
- Deviation from the default worker contract: survey workers edit ONLY their
  step file and asset file — the steering session owns this brief (four
  concurrent writers on one file is how briefs get clobbered).

## Decision ledger

- [Register the Observer Brain as a Wiki Root](./register-observer-brain-root.svx)
  — done: `observer` root in brain-roots.json (dark-wizard `e03b805`), 23
  pages catalog cleanly; live on next wiki build.
- [Survey Capture & Condense](./survey-capture-condense.svx) — capture
  working (652 live observation pages); dreams wobbly (nightly no-op is
  corpus youth, not the cap — but `slice(0, cap)` starvation is real and
  `capped:true` daily since 07-15); retros are a gap (2 files, no writer);
  release/dev drift found live.
- [Survey Brain Stores](./survey-brain-stores.svx) — 31 `.brain` trees on
  flagg, 4 registered; renderer working; ratchet wobbly (1 repo lints, 11
  unratcheted `.md`); graph wobbly (stale 07-12 data, and a rebuild would
  leak sensitive node metadata — boundary missing in graph-builder).
- [Survey Curation & Delivery](./survey-curation-delivery.svx) — every hop
  working except delivery policy (wobbly: legacy path live, fixed acting
  path dark); taste loop PROVEN closed: Joel's real 👍 graded
  `2026-07-17-248a3715344a` → `outcome: "worked"`, and outcomes feed
  `{{history}}` on the next beat.

## Latent

- Should the wiki page regenerate on a schedule (observer tick? dream
  pipeline?) instead of on-demand — and what would keep its verdicts honest?
- Settled by survey-capture-condense: today's eligiblePages 0 is corpus
  youth (nothing 7 days old yet), not the cap — but the cap starvation
  mechanism is real code and will bite as post-cap pages age; deserves its
  own fix step after this effort.
- Observer release promotion is manual and drifted live (release lacked the
  priority-high DM commit until the 2026-07-17 ~17:10Z promotion) — does
  release promotion deserve a receipt-checked script?

## Out of scope

- Fixing what the review finds. Verdicts and receipts end this effort; each
  `wobbly`/`gap` that deserves work gets its own step or effort afterward.
- The Brain Graph build-out (`brain-graph` effort owns it); this page only
  reports its current state.
